@apaddock I will say that the trick I used in e-Builder to create the resize handler (in planning module) was to set `position: absolute; float: right; z-index:200; right:-3px; width: 7px` on the drag handler.

This allows the drag handler to be overtop the border instead of strictly beside it within the header completely.  What I don't enjoy about most resize handlers is that I expect to be able to drag the border but can't and have to move my mouse over to the left at least a pixel in order to get the handler.  The above solved for that.  There may be more modern ways to do the same thing.  I'd be curious if something like this can be implemented, as it would create a larger target and a more intuitive one.  

