description:
The Data Table should support row actions with a button on the right side of each row

Since this will most likely just be a little of icon/text, the model can look something like this:
```ts
interface RowAction {
  display: {
    icon?: string;
    text: string;
  }
  id: string;
}
```

The consumer should be able to pass in an array of these `RowAction` objects. Then when a user clicks on one of the row actions, an event is emitted:
```ts
interface RowActionEvent {
  rowActionId: string;
  rowId: string;
}
```

This way the consumer can receive the event 'Delete action performed on row 13' and then do the necessary work on their end

