description:
Currently, Modus Web components doesn't provide a way to customize styling for its components because it uses shadow DOM mode, and the code inside shadow DOM is encapsulated which cannot be styled from outside. 
So we need custom properties that can penetrate the shadow DOM.

@ryan-henness-trimble @jeffdoolittle @coliff please correct me if am wrong.

comments:
> What are some use cases for custom CSS? My first thought is that we should try to provide everything the dev may need through the component API

One of the main reasons why using CSS Custom Properties would be helpful is for the adoption of dark mode theme, but also if we could share the common variables between all frameworks then it could help keeping them in sync easier to maintain.

